1
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:20,892
The New Republic Magazine was
first published in 1914.

2
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:25,336
it has been a fixture of American
political commentary ever since.

3
00:00:26,776 --> 00:00:29,802
in May of 1998, its staff was
comprised of 15 writer/editors.

4
00:00:30,013 --> 00:00:33,779
Their median age was 26.

5
00:00:33,984 --> 00:00:39,354
The youngest among them was
Stephen Glass.

6
00:00:46,730 --> 00:00:48,960
There's so many show-offs
in journalism...

7
00:00:49,165 --> 00:00:50,792
...so many braggarts and jerks.

8
00:00:51,001 --> 00:00:53,469
They're always selling,
always working the room...

9
00:00:53,670 --> 00:00:57,231
...always trying to make themselves
look hotter than they actually are.

10
00:00:57,440 --> 00:01:01,843
The good news is, reporters like that
make it easy to distinguish yourself.

11
00:01:02,045 --> 00:01:03,910
lf you're even a little bit humble...

12
00:01:04,114 --> 00:01:07,208
...a little self-effacing or solicitous,
you stand out.

13
00:01:07,417 --> 00:01:10,147
So you bring a co-worker lunch
if he's under deadline.

14
00:01:10,353 --> 00:01:11,843
You remember birthdays.

15
00:01:12,055 --> 00:01:15,183
it's true, journalism is hard work.
Everybody's under pressure.

16
00:01:15,392 --> 00:01:18,623
Everybody grinds to get the issue out.
Nobody gets any sleep...

17
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:22,093
...but you are allowed to smile
every once in a while.

18
00:01:22,299 --> 00:01:25,791
Even Woodward and Bernstein
went out for a burger now and then...

19
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:28,027
...and they won a Pulitzer.

20
00:01:29,773 --> 00:01:33,539
Some reporters think political content
makes a story memorable.

21
00:01:33,743 --> 00:01:37,543
l think it's the people you find,
their quirks, their flaws...

22
00:01:37,747 --> 00:01:40,614
...what makes them funny,
what makes them human.

23
00:01:40,817 --> 00:01:43,786
Journalism is just
the art of capturing behaviour.

24
00:01:43,987 --> 00:01:46,922
