who you're writing for.

27
00:01:51,328 --> 00:01:53,489
And you have to know
what you're good at.

28
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:55,358
l record what people do.

29
00:01:55,565 --> 00:01:58,500
l find out what moves them,
what scares them...

30
00:01:58,702 --> 00:02:02,695
...and l write that down. That way,
they're the ones telling the story.

31
00:02:02,906 --> 00:02:04,271
And you know what?

32
00:02:04,474 --> 00:02:07,375
Those kind of pieces
can win Pulitzers too.

