lf l were to throw a party...

98
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:45,874
...where all we did was play Monopoly,
would you guys come?

99
00:07:46,082 --> 00:07:49,313
-Could l be the little shoe?
-Of course.

100
00:07:49,619 --> 00:07:52,611
The lawyers have asked us
to tone down the cover on Serbia.

101
00:07:52,822 --> 00:07:54,585
Yeah, they fear charges of libel.

102
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:57,658
l know a little bit of libel law.

103
00:07:57,860 --> 00:08:01,125
it's only relevant if said person
has been out of the public eye.

104
00:08:01,330 --> 00:08:05,357
Well, yeah, so there's Serbia, hidden,
unknown to the world at large...

105
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:08,628
...until it appeared on the cover
of The New Republic.

106
00:08:08,838 --> 00:08:12,399
-With our weekly circulation of 80,000.
-Eighty-one five.

107
00:08:12,608 --> 00:08:14,599
-You done with it, Rob?
-Two days, tops.

108
00:08:14,811 --> 00:08:16,472
Yes, two days from Hanukkah.

109
00:08:16,679 --> 00:08:19,170
Hey, it's basically finished,
for the most part.

110
00:08:19,382 --> 00:08:21,577
Next up. Amy?

111
00:08:23,019 --> 00:08:25,419
Just finished the piece
on ethanol subsidies.

112
00:08:26,189 --> 00:08:29,590
There are 16,800 magazines
in this country...

113
00:08:29,792 --> 00:08:33,853
...but only one calls itself the in-flight
magazine of Air Force One.

114
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:37,160
And that's the thrill of working
at The New Republic.

115
00:08:37,366 --> 00:08:39,834
You're underpaid,
the hours are brutal...

116
00:08:40,036 --> 00:08:42,869
...but what you write gets read
by people who matter.

117
00:08:43,072 --> 00:08:44,733
Presidents, lawmakers--

118
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:48,308
Your work can actually
influence public policy.

119
00:08:48,511 --> 00:08:53,141
That's an amazing privilege
and a huge responsibility.

120
00:08:54,217 --> 00:08:58,654
I'm sorry, they don't want the whole
journalistic-responsibility speech.

121
00:08:58,988 --> 00:09:00,455
Do you?

122
00:09:01,491 --> 00:09:04,358
You just wanna know how
to get your name in print, right?

123
00:09:06,462 --> 00:09:08,054
Sounds familiar.

124
00:09:08,264 --> 00:09:12,826
Okay. Let me take you through
the life of your typical piece...

125
00:09:13,035 --> 00:09:15,026
...so you can see
where the hurdles are.

126
00:09:15,238 --> 00:09:17,297
We'll use one l wrote last year...

127
00:09:17,507 --> 00:09:20,965
...about a bunch of young Republicans
at a conservatives convention.

128
00:09:21,177 --> 00:09:23,202
Journalism is about pursuing
the truth...

129
00:09:23,412 --> 00:09:24,379
Spring Breakdown

130
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:28,175
...and l would never encourage you
to do anything sneaky or dishonest...

131
00:09:28,384 --> 00:09:32,684
...in pursuit of a story,
such as assuming a phoney identity.

132
00:09:32,889 --> 00:09:36,052
1997 CPAC Conference,
Washington's Omni Shoreham Hotel

133
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:41,321
l don't know, man, it seemed like
a pretty good turnout to me.

134
00:09:41,531 --> 00:09:44,898
No, man, conservatism's dead.

135
00:09:45,101 --> 00:09:47,035
-Dead?
-We're lost.

136
00:09:47,236 --> 00:09:48,760
Damn straight!

137
00:09:49,739 --> 00:09:52,105
On a story like that,
your notes are crucial.

138
00:09:52,308 --> 00:09:54,742
You have to record
everything you see and hear...

139
00:09:54,944 --> 00:09:56,878
...every quote, every detail...

140
00:09:57,079 --> 00:09:59,877
...all the way down
to the mini-bottles in the fridge.

141
00:10:00,082 --> 00:10:02,550
We're like this guy who has to pee:

142
00:10:02,819 --> 00:10:05,879
Lost in the desert looking for a tree.

143
00:10:06,088 --> 00:10:08,556
-it's true.
-Completely true.

144
00:10:13,196 --> 00:10:15,528
You guys know what
you're shopping for, right?

145
00:10:15,731 --> 00:10:16,993
Totally.

146
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:19,458
Get us a real heifer.

147
00:10:19,936 --> 00:10:23,633
The fatter the better.
