Just consider that for a second.

945
01:05:40,419 --> 01:05:44,480
You know? He sat down and he
hand-wrote a bunch of phoney quotes...

946
01:05:44,690 --> 01:05:47,818
...and he handed them in as
source material for the fact-check.

947
01:05:48,027 --> 01:05:50,325
- Doesn't that offend you?
- Of course it does.

948
01:05:50,529 --> 01:05:53,396
He lied to his editor.
That's supposed to offend you too.

949
01:05:53,599 --> 01:05:56,466
He's a confused, distraught kid,
obviously, Chuck.

950
01:05:56,669 --> 01:05:59,695
So suspend him for a couple months,
but let's not bury him.

951
01:05:59,905 --> 01:06:01,532
Suspend him.

952
01:06:02,141 --> 01:06:06,976
There are also political considerations
to take into account here:

953
01:06:07,580 --> 01:06:10,140
The rest of the staff,
the way they feel about him.

954
01:06:10,749 --> 01:06:12,216
l already know all that.

955
01:06:12,418 --> 01:06:17,515
What I'm saying is, if you fire him,
some of these people will leave.

956
01:06:18,424 --> 01:06:21,689
l don't know if we'd still have a
magazine at the end of the day.

957
01:06:24,864 --> 01:06:26,855
-Hey, Caitlin.
-Not now, David.

958
01:06:31,403 --> 01:06:34,304
-How's he doing?
-Well, he's a wreck, of course.

959
01:06:35,674 --> 01:06:38,871
-l want him in here, Caitlin.
-He's too scared to come in here.

960
01:06:39,078 --> 01:06:42,673
He thinks you want to destroy him.
He knows what he did was horrible.

961
01:06:43,249 --> 01:06:45,217
He knows how badly he messed up.

962
01:06:45,417 --> 01:06:48,079
The part he's most upset about
is lying to you, Chuck.

963
01:06:48,287 --> 01:06:52,519
He knows you took it as a sign of
disrespect instead of as a panic move.

964
01:06:52,725 --> 01:06:54,886
Think about the workload
he's been carrying.

965
01:06:55,127 --> 01:06:56,526
All this and classes.

966
01:06:56,729 --> 01:06:59,289
He hasn't slept more than
two hours in nine months.

967
01:06:59,732 --> 01:07:02,292
He got a little sloppy
and lied to cover his tracks.

968
01:07:02,501 --> 01:07:04,526
-He's sick about it.
-Caitlin...

969
01:07:04,737 --> 01:07:08,605
...the building he described,
it doesn't even exist.

970
01:07:09,108 --> 01:07:10,575
He just made it up.

971
01:07:13,112 --> 01:07:14,340
So....

972
01:07:22,087 --> 01:07:23,748
Obviously, he needs some help.

973
01:07:26,258 --> 01:07:28,283
-He needs help.
-Just get him in here.

974
01:07:28,494 --> 01:07:30,621
You can't fire him.

975
01:07:31,297 --> 01:07:35,097
l don't think he'll survive. You don't
understand, we're all he has.

976
01:07:37,002 --> 01:07:38,936
You can't fire him, Chuck.

977
01:07:42,374 --> 01:07:43,671
Thanks, Lew.

978
01:08:07,666 --> 01:08:09,497
Would you guys excuse us
for a minute?

979
01:08:17,643 --> 01:08:20,111
Chuck isn't firing Steve...

980
01:08:23,315 --> 01:08:27,012
He's just suspending him
for two years.

981
01:08:34,994 --> 01:08:37,690
l think l have to quit.
Caitlin

982
01:08:39,498 --> 01:08:41,466
SEND TO:

983
01:08:42,801 --> 01:08:44,769
michael.kelly@nationaljourn

984
01:08:48,040 --> 01:08:49,405
Sending...

985
01:08:55,948 --> 01:08:59,213
--watered-down stock and,
you know, within....

986
01:09:00,252 --> 01:09:01,617
Steve.

987
01:09:08,093 --> 01:09:09,424
What are you doing here?

988
01:09:10,729 --> 01:09:12,663
I'm so dead.

989
01:09:13,465 --> 01:09:15,228
l mean, I'm over.

990
01:09:16,935 --> 01:09:19,267
Nobody's ever gonna
hire me again, are they?

991
01:09:20,873 --> 01:09:24,400
l was so sloppy,
trusting my sources like that.

992
01:09:24,610 --> 01:09:28,307
And then lying about it.
And to Chuck of all people.

993
01:09:28,514 --> 01:09:33,281
l mean, the one guy
who's hated me all along.

994
01:09:34,153 --> 01:09:35,780
I'm sure that it's not personal.

995
01:09:35,988 --> 01:09:37,182
No?

996
01:09:38,023 --> 01:09:40,753
Chuck keeps a list in his head...

997
01:09:40,959 --> 01:09:44,190
...of everybody who's
a Michael Kelly person.

998
01:09:44,396 --> 01:09:46,626
A couple of times...

999
01:09:46,832 --> 01:09:50,324
...l said some things
l shouldn't have said about you.

1000
01:09:50,536 --> 01:09:52,003
So now I'm on it.

1001
01:09:53,172 --> 01:09:55,470
That's why he's so set
on killing me now.

1002
01:09:55,674 --> 01:09:58,973
Well, l have to tell you, Steve,
he's within his rights.

1003
01:09:59,178 --> 01:10:02,204
The things you did
were fireable offenses.

1004
01:10:02,414 --> 01:10:05,281
l know. I'm not saying
that they weren't.

1005
01:10:06,685 --> 01:10:10,712
l did some terrible, terrible things.

1006
01:10:14,193 --> 01:10:17,219
But believe me, Michael,
Chuck doesn't care about any of it.

1007
01:10:17,763 --> 01:10:21,255
it's my loyalty to you
that he's punishing me for.

1008
01:10:22,000 --> 01:10:23,968
I'm such an idiot.

1009
01:10:24,970 --> 01:10:27,131
Now who's gonna hire me?

1010
01:10:28,974 --> 01:10:31,534
Steve, l have to ask you something.

1011
01:10:35,280 --> 01:10:37,840
Did you ever cook a piece
when l was your boss?

1012
01:10:40,018 --> 01:10:42,248
Did you ever lie to me?

1013
01:10:43,655 --> 01:10:47,216
The young-conservatives piece,
the mini-bottles....

1014
01:10:48,293 --> 01:10:49,590
Was that true?

1015
01:11:08,280 --> 01:11:10,441
-Hello?
-Chuck, it's David Bach.

1016
01:11:10,649 --> 01:11:13,447
I'm really sorry to bother you,
but it seemed important.

1017
01:11:14,620 --> 01:11:18,716
- it's fine. is there a problem?
- Well, l don't know.

1018
01:11:18,924 --> 01:11:21,893
l just got off the phone with Stephen.
He sounds horrible.

1019
01:11:22,094 --> 01:11:25,188
-Did you suspend him, Chuck?
-David....

1020
01:11:27,299 --> 01:11:28,789
What is the problem?

1021
01:11:29,001 --> 01:11:32,027
He asked me if l would drive him
out to Dulles later tonight.

1022
01:11:32,237 --> 01:11:34,728
He wasn't sure he'd
be safe driving by himself.

1023
01:11:34,940 --> 01:11:37,636
l just thought l should
draw your attention to that.

1024
01:11:37,943 --> 01:11:39,535
Did he say where he was going?

1025
01:11:39,745 --> 01:11:42,475
Yeah, he said he'd be staying
with family for a while.

1026
01:11:42,681 --> 01:11:46,208
-That can be only one of two places.
-His parents live in Highland Park.

1027
01:11:46,418 --> 01:11:49,945
Yeah, or his brother out in Palo Aito.

1028
01:11:50,689 --> 01:11:53,157
-I'm sorry?
-Yeah, his brother at Stanford.

1029
01:11:54,493 --> 01:11:55,824
Chuck?

1030
01:12:13,812 --> 01:12:16,474
You had your brother pose
as George Sims.

1031
01:12:16,915 --> 01:12:19,179
-What?
-The phoney recording...

1032
01:12:19,384 --> 01:12:22,410
...from Jukt Micronics.
it's a Palo Aito number...

1033
01:12:22,621 --> 01:12:25,215
...and your brother's at Stanford.
He posed as Sims.

1034
01:12:25,424 --> 01:12:28,757
No, Sims is a real guy.
I've talked to him a million times.

1035
01:12:28,961 --> 01:12:32,453
-My brother and l aren't speaking now.
-Stop it. You faked Sims.

1036
01:12:32,664 --> 01:12:35,724
-You faked the website, voice mails...
-You don't know, Chuck.

1037
01:12:35,934 --> 01:12:38,368
-...Restil, Hiert, Ghort.
-You got this backwards.

1038
01:12:38,570 --> 01:12:41,698
it's all crap. l can trace it.
I'll find it all billed to you--

1039
01:12:41,907 --> 01:12:44,899
What are you talking about?
Those are all real people.

1040
01:12:45,110 --> 01:12:46,941
-They are?
-Yeah.

1041
01:12:48,947 --> 01:12:50,744
Look at me...

1042
01:12:52,651 --> 01:12:53,879
...and say that again.

1043
01:12:55,020 --> 01:12:57,181
Those are all real people.

1044
01:13:02,894 --> 01:13:04,088
Okay.

1045
01:13:06,098 --> 01:13:07,895
l want you out of here.

1046
01:13:08,700 --> 01:13:10,668
-What?
-l want you out of here.

1047
01:13:11,937 --> 01:13:13,996
And you can't take anything with you.

1048
01:13:14,773 --> 01:13:17,333
There are some files.
l have to put them on a disk.

1049
01:13:17,876 --> 01:13:20,140
-No.
-No, they're mine. Personal stuff!

1050
01:13:20,345 --> 01:13:21,744
l don't care.

1051
01:13:25,684 --> 01:13:26,946
l know you don't.

1052
01:13:28,320 --> 01:13:29,844
-Can l shut down--?
-Don't!

1053
01:13:30,055 --> 01:13:31,545
I'm in the middle of a file.

1054
01:13:31,757 --> 01:13:33,588
-Goddamn it.
-Back away from the desk.

1055
01:13:33,859 --> 01:13:35,918
-Leave it, or I'll call security.
-Christ.

1056
01:13:36,128 --> 01:13:37,425
Okay?

1057
01:13:42,100 --> 01:13:43,658
Can l take my Rolodex?

1058
01:13:45,604 --> 01:13:46,798
Steve....

1059
01:13:49,608 --> 01:13:52,805
-Can l take my law books?
-Sure.

1060
01:13:57,215 --> 01:13:59,877
Look, I'm gonna need to have
your security key.

1061
01:14:03,221 --> 01:14:05,052
I'm not a criminal, Chuck.

1062
01:14:08,293 --> 01:14:09,692
Okay?

1063
01:14:12,564 --> 01:14:16,056
-I'm not a criminal.
-Oh, l heard you.

1064
01:14:16,335 --> 01:14:17,666
Come on.

1065
01:14:39,691 --> 01:14:41,318
Chuck?

1066
01:14:52,471 --> 01:14:53,938
l said l was sorry.

1067
01:14:54,473 --> 01:14:55,838
l know.

1068
01:14:57,476 --> 01:14:59,068
But you have to go.

1069
01:16:01,706 --> 01:16:04,800
Bond traders, as a rule, do not have
much time to loaf around.

1070
01:16:05,010 --> 01:16:07,535
And the Wall Street
investment house RVL...

1071
01:16:07,746 --> 01:16:10,078
...takes its work ethic
to a particularly--

1072
01:16:10,816 --> 01:16:13,182
One trader is now testing
a hand-held urinal...

1073
01:16:13,385 --> 01:16:15,785
...normally used by cops
on stakeouts--

1074
01:16:17,656 --> 01:16:19,453
After Mike Tyson was disqualified...

1075
01:16:19,658 --> 01:16:22,821
...for biting Evander Holyfield,
l offered several talk shows...

1076
01:16:23,028 --> 01:16:26,520
...my services as a biting expert.
I'm someone who knows--

1077
01:16:27,132 --> 01:16:29,600
The minibar is open,
and empty bottles of booze...

1078
01:16:29,801 --> 01:16:31,792
...are scattered on the carpet--

1079
01:16:32,003 --> 01:16:33,561
it was the monthly gathering...

1080
01:16:33,772 --> 01:16:36,798
...of the Commission to Restore
the Presidency to Greatness--

1081
01:16:37,008 --> 01:16:39,067
Patriotic profits
will have a hard time...

1082
01:16:39,277 --> 01:16:41,438
...holding back this
merchandising bonanza--

1083
01:16:41,646 --> 01:16:44,479
Western Union now
has a stop the Cassini hotline...

1084
01:16:44,683 --> 01:16:48,517
...which forwards anti-Cassini
telegrams to the White House.

1085
01:16:48,720 --> 01:16:52,884
--called ''Loving Lewinsky'' that looks
and works like a child's doll....

1086
01:17:01,333 --> 01:17:04,427
-Thanks, George. Sorry for the trouble.
-No problem, Steve.

1087
01:17:19,518 --> 01:17:20,883
Chuck?

1088
01:17:27,325 --> 01:17:30,488
The thing with George Sims...

1089
01:17:31,496 --> 01:17:33,361
...that was....

1090
01:17:33,565 --> 01:17:36,363
The voice you heard
on the telephone...

1091
01:17:37,636 --> 01:17:39,900
...that was my brother. I'm sorry.

1092
01:17:44,276 --> 01:17:49,043
There really is a George Sims.
I've spoken to him a million times.

1093
01:17:49,247 --> 01:17:51,181
He just stopped talking to me.

1094
01:17:52,183 --> 01:17:56,085
You know, because of the article.
He was so mad about it.

1095
01:17:56,288 --> 01:17:57,880
l didn't know what to do.

1096
01:17:58,089 --> 01:18:00,614
The guys from Forbes
were putting pressure on me.

1097
01:18:00,825 --> 01:18:03,316
You know? And you were so mad.

1098
01:18:03,528 --> 01:18:06,520
l just thought that if l could
get everybody off my back...

1099
01:18:06,731 --> 01:18:08,198
...okay, for just a day....

1100
01:18:09,034 --> 01:18:11,798
Just a day would give me
enough time to go and find him.

1101
01:18:12,003 --> 01:18:14,267
You can understand that, can't you?

1102
01:18:15,707 --> 01:18:17,299
You're fired, Steve.

1103
01:18:18,610 --> 01:18:19,941
What?

1104
01:18:21,212 --> 01:18:24,579
You're fired. You've lost your job.

1105
01:18:28,086 --> 01:18:29,883
But you can't--

1106
01:18:56,281 --> 01:18:57,839
Chuck...

1107
01:18:59,117 --> 01:19:01,642
...will you please
take me to the airport?

1108
01:19:03,054 --> 01:19:04,282
Jesus.

1109
01:19:04,522 --> 01:19:06,114
Please, okay?

1110
01:19:07,459 --> 01:19:11,486
You don't have to talk to me
if you don't want to. it's fine.

1111
01:19:13,298 --> 01:19:15,630
But l can't be by myself right now.

1112
01:19:17,102 --> 01:19:18,626
Okay? I'm....

1113
01:19:21,106 --> 01:19:22,971
I'm afraid of what I'm gonna do.

1114
01:19:23,441 --> 01:19:27,434
And you know,
l can't get there by myself.

1115
01:19:30,448 --> 01:19:32,678
I'm not going anywhere with you.

1116
01:19:32,884 --> 01:19:35,876
lf you feel you're a danger to yourself,
you can sit down...

1117
01:19:36,087 --> 01:19:37,884
...until you feel calm enough to go.

1118
01:19:38,089 --> 01:19:39,886
But I'm not going anywhere with you.

1119
01:19:40,091 --> 01:19:45,154
But I'm afraid that I'm gonna
do something, okay?

1120
01:19:47,866 --> 01:19:51,666
-Did you hear what l said?
-Yeah.

1121
01:19:53,938 --> 01:19:55,530
it's a hell of a story.

1122
01:19:59,778 --> 01:20:01,245
Chuck, please?

1123
01:20:02,681 --> 01:20:06,310
Stop pitching, Steve. it's over.

1124
01:20:12,123 --> 01:20:13,317
Okay.

1125
01:20:40,118 --> 01:20:43,849
''Spring Breakdown,'' ''The Jungle''...

1126
01:20:44,055 --> 01:20:50,483
...''A Fine Mess,'' ''After the Fall,''
''Peddling Poppy''...

1127
01:20:50,929 --> 01:20:56,492
...''CheapSuits,'' ''Kicked Out,''
''No Free Launch''...

1128
01:20:56,701 --> 01:21:00,364
...''Ratted Out,'' ''State of Nature,''
''Clutch Situation''...

1129
01:21:00,572 --> 01:21:05,066
...''All Wet,'' ''Plotters,''
''Praised be Greenspan''...

1130
01:21:05,276 --> 01:21:09,372
...''Monica Selis,'' ''Hack Heaven.''

1131
01:21:18,022 --> 01:21:21,822
What the hell did you do to Steve?
He just called from his car, hysterical.

1132
01:21:22,060 --> 01:21:25,393
-l asked what was wrong. He said--
-l fired him, okay?

1133
01:21:31,302 --> 01:21:33,827
Not suspended, fired.

1134
01:21:35,140 --> 01:21:37,301
This wasn't
an isolated incident, Caitlin.

1135
01:21:37,509 --> 01:21:39,340
He cooked a dozen of them,
maybe more.

1136
01:21:39,944 --> 01:21:42,344
We're gonna have to go through them.
All of them.

1137
01:21:42,647 --> 01:21:45,241
The only one was ''Hack Heaven.''
He told me that.

1138
01:21:45,450 --> 01:21:48,442
lf he were a stranger, a guy you
were doing a piece about...

1139
01:21:48,653 --> 01:21:50,951
...pretend that guy told you
he'd done it once.

1140
01:21:51,156 --> 01:21:52,680
Would you take his word for it?

1141
01:21:52,891 --> 01:21:55,052
Of course not.
You'd dig, and you'd bury him!

1142
01:21:55,260 --> 01:21:57,421
You'd be offended
if anyone told you not to.

1143
01:21:57,629 --> 01:22:01,656
-All those pieces were fact-checked--
-So was ''Hack Heaven''!

1144
01:22:06,004 --> 01:22:07,699
You're a good reporter.

1145
01:22:07,906 --> 01:22:10,204
You've always been a smart,
thorough reporter.

1146
01:22:10,408 --> 01:22:12,103
Why can't you be one now?

1147
01:22:12,310 --> 01:22:15,074
Because what you're telling me
is impossible, Chuck.

1148
01:22:15,480 --> 01:22:17,641
Go upstairs.

1149
01:22:17,849 --> 01:22:20,477
-Read them again.
-This is bullshit!

1150
01:22:20,685 --> 01:22:24,280
Go all the way back, because half
of them ran when Mike was still here.

1151
01:22:26,724 --> 01:22:29,249
That's what this is. Of course.

1152
01:22:29,460 --> 01:22:30,950
What are you gonna do, Chuck?

1153
01:22:31,529 --> 01:22:32,757
Pick us off one by one...

1154
01:22:32,964 --> 01:22:36,161
...everybody loyal to Mike, till you
have a staff belonging to you?

1155
01:22:36,367 --> 01:22:38,267
is that the kind of magazine
you'd run?

1156
01:22:38,469 --> 01:22:40,960
When this thing blows,
there won't be a magazine.

1157
01:22:41,539 --> 01:22:44,269
lf you wanna make this about Mike,
l don't give a shit.

1158
01:22:44,475 --> 01:22:47,137
You can resent me, hate me,
but come Monday morning...

1159
01:22:47,345 --> 01:22:50,109
...we'll all have to answer
for what we let happen here.

1160
01:22:50,315 --> 01:22:52,715
We're all gonna have
an apology to make.

1161
01:22:52,917 --> 01:22:56,318
Jesus Christ! Do you have any idea
how much shit we're about to eat?

1162
01:22:56,521 --> 01:23:00,048
Every competitor.... They're gonna
pounce, and they should.

1163
01:23:00,258 --> 01:23:02,158
Because we blew it, Caitlin.

1164
01:23:03,328 --> 01:23:07,856
He handed us fiction after fiction,
and we printed them all as fact.

1165
01:23:09,033 --> 01:23:10,660
Just because...

1166
01:23:11,069 --> 01:23:13,162
...we found him entertaining.

1167
01:23:15,940 --> 01:23:18,033
it's indefensible.

1168
01:23:18,977 --> 01:23:20,877
Don't you know that?

1169
01:23:36,861 --> 01:23:40,297
Monday, May 11, 1998

1170
01:23:59,584 --> 01:24:02,052
is everyone in the conference room?

1171
01:24:05,356 --> 01:24:07,415
You know what
could've prevented all this?

1172
01:24:08,059 --> 01:24:09,390
No, what?

1173
01:24:10,929 --> 01:24:12,794
Pictures.

1174
01:24:13,631 --> 01:24:15,360
How could you make up characters...

1175
01:24:15,566 --> 01:24:18,467
...if everyone you wrote about
had to be photographed?

1176
01:24:26,544 --> 01:24:31,277
You know, Stephen, if you wanted to,
you could do these kids a giant favor.

1177
01:24:31,482 --> 01:24:33,746
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

1178
01:24:37,288 --> 01:24:40,121
You could write something boring
one of these days.

1179
01:24:41,392 --> 01:24:44,225
Give them a little less to live up to.

1180
01:24:44,929 --> 01:24:46,590
l suppose l could.

1181
